translations:
‘Schatir
			Schumān kaufte fünf Kilo Garn, wickelte sie um sein Dach herum
			und machte einen Strang daraus’; 25/36 [MT];

‘She prepared a dinner for him. He says: “What dinner have you
			prepared?” She answers “I have prepared a sweet one”’;
			41/7-8 - note the parallelism with 41/9 where

‘Der
			Jüngling, der sich zum Mädchen gemacht hatte, antwortete [ihr]’;
			29/65; 29/380;

‘It was midday. Suddenly they saw a woman: she has come and has
			brought a plate of rice and a goose on top of it. She has cooked
			it, roasted it, put it on top of the dish and has come’ 76/56;

‘Donnerwetter,
			ich hatte vor, mir auch noch eine Pluderhose davon machen zu
			lassen, doch du hast es nicht zugelassen’;

‘Ich
			gehe zu dem Lichte dort und sehe, was Gott (mit mir) tun wird’;
			26/149;

‘I
			said: “It will be very good, if you do this thing”.’ JL
			9.9.5;

‘If
			you lay your hands on him, you know what I will do with you!’;
			40/15 [MT];

‘He would come and give her medicine, herbs and other things,
			(but) he could not do anything with her (to make her feel better)’
			78/212;

And
			the buttermilk… they, who wished to make the yoghurt, made it’
			JL 12.14.8;

‘He gave her some other bath, it was not the bath. He said:
			“Wash yourself!” – She did so, but it had no effect (on
			her), she did not become cured’ 78/229;
